bridge-mgr: port to the qca_ppe EDMA stack, drop ssdk/bond/OVS/vlan-mgr

nss-bridge-mgr offloads Linux-bridge L2 forwarding into the NSS firmware
by registering a firmware bridge interface and binding the member ports'
PPE VSI to it. Upstream does the PPE side through qca-ssdk (fal_*, ref_vsi,
ppe_port_vsi_*) and depends on vlan-mgr + bonding, none of which exist on
the EDMA/qca_ppe stack.

Re-point the PPE backend onto qca_ppe, which is the single writer of the
PPE tables and already allocates one shared VSI per Linux bridge when its
DSA user ports join (port_bridge_join) with the member/flood masks
programmed. bridge-mgr now only adds the firmware-side layer:

  - register the bridge dynamic interface (unchanged),
  - reuse qca_ppe's bridge VSI via qca_ppe_bridge_vsi_get() instead of
    allocating its own; qca_ppe keeps ownership and frees it on leave,
  - re-assert the VSI member/flood masks with qca_ppe_bridge_vsi_refresh()
    after every firmware vsi_assign (the firmware zeroes them, same hazard
    as the per-port VSI),
  - flush a roamed MAC via qca_ppe_fdb_del() from the FDB notifier.

Dropped as unavailable / out of scope on this stack and for a home router:
the fal_* fdb-learn toggles (qca_ppe enables learning already), the bonding
paths (no qca bonding patches), the L2-exception ACL block (PPE virtual
ports only), the WAN-interface sysctl, OVS (compile-gated off), and the
VLAN-over-bridge path (no vlan-mgr) - VLAN members simply fall back to the
software bridge. STP sync stays: it is the DSA .port_stp_state_set op in
qca_ppe, independent of bridge-mgr.

The PPE port-table VSI is no longer written here (qca_ppe's DSA bridge_join
owns it), which avoids two writers racing on the same table.

bridge-mgr loads at runtime, after the bridge already exists. A netdevice
notifier only replays NETDEV_REGISTER/UP, not NETDEV_CHANGEUPPER, so
register_br() walks the bridge's existing lower devices and joins them;
later members arrive via NETDEV_CHANGEUPPER as before.

Signed-off-by: Julius Bairaktaris <julius@bairaktaris.de>

